{"key":"post-8888476","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>8888476</id>\n<content>I used the crystals a few years ago with very poor results.&amp;nbsp; Loss of moisture from a substrate is one of the main pinning triggers.&amp;nbsp; If you try to maintain equilibrium, you end up with crappy pinsets.&amp;nbsp; The key is to get the substrate damp, and then let it dry out slightly before adding more moisture.&amp;nbsp; This back and forth produces the best bang for the buck.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;font class=&quot;small&quot;&gt;Quote:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;RR - Would you suggest adding verm to an 80:20 coir to coffee substrate? &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;font class=&quot;post&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Yes.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>8888970</next>\n<prev>8888331</prev>\n<first>8884224</first>\n<last>8889047</last>\n<when>1220756934</when>\n<utime>09/07/08 06:08 AM</utime>\n</post>"}